HEADWORD: Playa
<hw>Pla"ya</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>A
beach; a strand; in the plains and deserts of Texas, New Mexico, and
Arizona, a broad, level spot, on which subsequently becomes dry by
evaporation.</def> <rj><au>Bartlett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

